  "notes": "ANTI-OVERCLAIM: this packet proves only a known COMPANION counterexample (Steinerberger's disproof of the multiplicative analogue), not Erdos #494's original sum-based question. Proof authority: Lean kernel via the tracked proof-search loop (episode d4688926, problem_version 6222e446-02cc-4315-a065-bd7434530fb3), submitted as a SubmitModule (1 helper def prodMultiset + 1 helper theorem prodMultiset_map_mul + root theorem erdos_494_product), kernel_verified on the second submission: the first attempt used the unqualified `mapEmbedding` name relying on the sibling repo's `open Finset` (module_items have no room for an `open` preamble), which elaborated to a metavariable and broke a `rw`; fully qualifying it as `Finset.mapEmbedding` fixed it cleanly. Independently re-verified in THIS environment's own pinned toolchain rather than treated as evidence merely because the sibling repo (F:\\Github\\mnehmos.llm-driven-proof-search.environment\\ErdosProblems\\erdos-494\\proof\\Erdos494_product.lean) already reports it kernel_verified there -- per this repo's evidence policy. training.eligibility: quarantined per the default-quarantine policy for open_problem_related packets pending real external review (same policy as the #399 and #349 packets). Third packet in the frontier/erdos lane.",
